# Task list + work log sync (TheaterOrStream)

## On every push (required)

**Before `git push`**, always update the work log so the user can `git pull` on phone and continue.

1. **Update** `.agent/implementation-work-log.md`:
   - Add or extend a **Session** section with: problem, files changed, behavior/result
   - Add row(s) to **Git commit history** table (commit hash + one-line summary)
   - Set **HEAD** line to the commit hash being pushed
   - Note **Next recommended** task if it changed
2. **Sync HEAD** in `.agent/tos-production-architecture-plan.md` and `.agent/implementation-plan-api-optimization.md`
3. **Include work log in the same push** as the code (same commit or immediate follow-up commit before push)
4. **Never push code-only** without an updated work log when the session changed behavior, files, or task status

### Work log session template

```markdown
## Session: [Month Year] — [short title]

### [Feature/fix name] ✅

**Problem:** …
**Files changed:** …
**Behavior:** …
```

---

## At session start (after pull or phone work)

1. **Discover what changed:** `git log --oneline -15`, diff vs `origin/main`
2. **Ask about off-git work:** Supabase SQL, Vercel env, deploys (won't be in git)
3. **Read** `.agent/implementation-work-log.md` first — it is the phone handoff source of truth

---

## Update ALL four task sources together

When task status changes, sync in one pass:

| Source | Path |
|--------|------|
| Work log | `.agent/implementation-work-log.md` |
| Repo master plan | `.agent/tos-production-architecture-plan.md` |
| API plan cross-ref | `.agent/implementation-plan-api-optimization.md` |
| Cursor plan | `~/.cursor/plans/tos_production_architecture_e5360011.plan.md` |

### Per-task updates

- YAML `todos[].status`: `completed` | `pending`
- Master table: ✅ Done · 🔄 Partial · ⬜ Pending
- **HEAD** → latest short hash · **Progress** (e.g. `4 / 14`)

---

## Do not

- Push without updating the work log when there is meaningful session work
- Leave Cursor plan stale while repo docs are updated
- Mark `db-migrations` or SQL tasks complete without user confirmation when run outside git
- Skip sync after user mentions phone, pull, push, or "I finished X"
